You are here: Home / Faculty : Tao JinFaculty : Tao Jin





Tao Jin
Associate Professor
Louisiana State University
School of Library and Information Science
273 Coates Hall
Baton Rouge, LA 70803
Phone: 225-578-1486
Fax: 225-578-4581
taojin@lsu.edu




PhD, Information Studies, McGill University
MLIS, McGill University
BA, English, Capital Normal University
 
Professional Experience: 


Associate Professor, School of Library and Information Science, Louisiana State University (2014-present)
Assistant Professor, School of Library and Information Science, Louisiana State University (2008-2014)
Instructor, School of Library and Information Science, Louisiana State University (2007-2008)
Sessional Lecturer and Research/Teaching Assistant, School of Information Studies, McGill University (2002-2007)
Associate Editor, Dow Jones & Company Inc. (1999-2000)


 


Leadership Positions/Service:


Executive Board Member and Treasurer, Competitive Intelligence Division of Special Libraries Association (2011-2013)
Program Committee Member for the American Society for Information Science and Technology (ASIS&T) 2009 Annual Meeting, Vancouver, Canada

 
Honors and Awards



The 2010 BRASS Emerald Research Grant Recipient, American Library Association (2010)
The 2009 SLA Research Grant Recipient, Special Libraries Association (2010)

 
Courses Taught
LIS 7013 Evaluation of Information Systems
LIS 7205 Business Information Resources
LIS 7403 Special Libraries and Information Centers
LIS 7508 Management of Knowledge-based Assets in Organizations
 
Areas of Interest
Competitive intelligence
Knowledge management
Business information seeking, processing and management
 
Selected Recent Publications
Jin. T., & Ju, B. (2014). “Toward understanding the perceptions of information professionals about competitive intelligence work.”  Journal of Information and Knowledge Management (JIKM), 13 (2):1450011 [22 pages], DOI: 10.1142/s02196492150017.
 
Jin, T., & Ju, B. (2014). “The Corporate Information Agency: Do Competitive Intelligence Practitioners Utilize It?” Journal of the Association for Information Science and Technology (JASIST).  65(3): 589-608. 
 
Ju, B., & Jin, T. (2013). “Incorporating Nonparametric Statistics into Delphi Studies in Library and Information science.” Information Research, 18(3), paper 589.   
 
Jin. T., & Bouthillier, F. (2012). “The Integration of Intelligence Analysis into LIS Education.” Journal of Education for Library and Information Science, 53(2): 130-148.
 
Selected Grants/Funded Project:
 
2014- The Peabody’s Society Dean’s Circle for Faculty Research Project, $3000, College of Human Sciences and Education, Louisiana State University, Project title: “Knowledge Management Portal as an Enabler for Trans-disciplinary Research Collaborations”.
 
 2009 –  Research Grant (Internal Award Number: 146-05-6102), Special Libraries Association, $20,314, Project title: “Understanding the Value of of Corporate Libraries in Competitive Intelligence Practices.” 4/1/2010-12/31/2011.
 
